---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';

const lastUpdated = 'April 28, 2026';
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy | Kanata Labs LLC"
  description="How Kanata Labs LLC collects, uses, and protects information on its corporate website."
>
  <Header />
  <main>
    <section class="page-hero">
      <div class="container">
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="subtitle">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-content">
      <div class="container">
        <article class="legal-body">
          <p class="lead">
            This Privacy Policy describes how Kanata Labs LLC
            (&ldquo;Kanata Labs,&rdquo; &ldquo;we,&rdquo; &ldquo;us,&rdquo;
            or &ldquo;our&rdquo;) collects, uses, and shares information
            in connection with this website at
            <strong>kanatalabs.com</strong>. It applies to information
            collected through this site only. Individual products and
            games we publish may have their own privacy notices, which
            are provided alongside those products.
          </p>

          <h2>1. Information we collect</h2>
          <p>
            <strong>Information you provide directly.</strong> If you
            contact us through the email address or contact form on
            this site, we receive the information you choose to send,
            such as your name, email address, and the contents of your
            message.
          </p>
          <p>
            <strong>Information collected automatically.</strong> When
            you visit this site, we and our analytics provider
            automatically receive certain technical information,
            including your IP address, approximate location derived
            from that IP address, browser type and version, device
            type, operating system, referring page, the pages you
            view, and the times of those visits.
          </p>

          <h2>2. How we use information</h2>
          <p>We use the information described above to:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Respond to inquiries and communicate with you;</li>
            <li>Operate, maintain, and improve this website;</li>
            <li>
              Understand how visitors use the site in aggregate, so we
              can improve content and structure;
            </li>
            <li>
              Detect and prevent fraud, abuse, and security incidents;
              and
            </li>
            <li>Comply with applicable legal obligations.</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>3. Cookies and analytics</h2>
          <p>
            This site uses Google Analytics 4, a service provided by
            Google LLC, to measure traffic and usage. Google Analytics
            uses cookies and similar technologies to collect the
            automatic information described above. You can learn more
            about how Google uses data when you use partner sites at
            <a href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/partner-sites" rel="noopener noreferrer">policies.google.com/technologies/partner-sites</a>,
            and you can opt out of Google Analytics by installing the
            Google Analytics Opt-out Browser Add-on at
            <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout" rel="noopener noreferrer">tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout</a>.
          </p>
          <p>
            Most browsers allow you to refuse cookies or delete cookies
            that have already been set. Doing so should not prevent
            you from using this site.
          </p>

          <h2>4. How we share information</h2>
          <p>
            We do not sell personal information. We share information
            only in the limited circumstances described below:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>
              <strong>Service providers.</strong> We use a small number
              of vendors to host this website, deliver email, and
              provide analytics. These providers process information
              on our behalf and only as necessary to provide their
              services.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Legal and safety.</strong> We may disclose
              information when we reasonably believe disclosure is
              required by law, legal process, or to protect the
              rights, property, or safety of Kanata Labs, our users,
              or the public.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Business transfers.</strong> If Kanata Labs is
              involved in a merger, acquisition, financing, or sale
              of assets, information may be transferred as part of
              that transaction, subject to standard confidentiality
              protections.
            </li>
          </ul>

          <h2>5. Data retention</h2>
          <p>
            We retain inquiry and contact information for as long as
            reasonably necessary to respond to your inquiry, to keep
            records of our communications, and to comply with our
            legal obligations. Aggregated analytics data may be
            retained for longer periods.
          </p>

          <h2>6. Your choices and rights</h2>
          <p>
            Depending on where you live, you may have rights with
            respect to the personal information we hold about you,
            including the right to access, correct, delete, or
            restrict its use, and the right to object to certain
            processing or to data portability. To exercise these
            rights, contact us using the details below. We may need
            to verify your identity before fulfilling a request.
          </p>
          <p>
            If you are located in the European Economic Area, the
            United Kingdom, or Switzerland, our legal bases for
            processing are typically your consent, the performance of
            a contract or pre-contract steps you request, our
            legitimate interests in operating and securing the site,
            and compliance with legal obligations.
          </p>

          <h2>7. Children</h2>
          <p>
            This website is intended for a general audience and is
            not directed at children under 13. We do not knowingly
            collect personal information from children under 13
            through this site. If you believe a child has provided
            information to us, please contact us so we can delete it.
          </p>

          <h2>8. Security</h2>
          <p>
            We use reasonable administrative, technical, and physical
            safeguards to protect information collected through this
            site. No method of transmission or storage is completely
            secure, however, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.
          </p>

          <h2>9. International transfers</h2>
          <p>
            Kanata Labs is based in the United States, and information
            collected through this site is processed in the United
            States and other countries where our service providers
            operate. By using this site, you understand that your
            information may be transferred to and processed in those
            countries.
          </p>

          <h2>10. Changes to this policy</h2>
          <p>
            We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When
            we do, we will revise the &ldquo;Last updated&rdquo; date
            at the top of this page. Material changes will be made
            clear on the site.
          </p>

          <h2>11. Contact us</h2>
          <p>
            For questions about this Privacy Policy or our handling
            of personal information, please use our
            <a href="/contact">contact form</a>. If you cannot use
            the form, you may instead write to
            <span class="obf">contact <span aria-hidden="true">[at]</span><span class="sr-only">@</span> kanatalabs.com</span>.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .page-hero {
    padding: 120px 0 60px;
    background-color: var(--color-off-white);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .page-hero h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-xs);
  }

  .subtitle {
    color: var(--color-gray);
    font-size: 1rem;
  }

  .legal-content {
    padding: var(--spacing-xl) 0;
  }

  .legal-body {
    max-width: 760px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    line-height: 1.75;
  }

  .legal-body .lead {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-lg);
  }

  .legal-body h2 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    margin-top: var(--spacing-lg);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-sm);
    color: var(--color-black);
  }

  .legal-body p {
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-sm);
  }

  .legal-body ul {
    margin: 0 0 var(--spacing-md) 1.25rem;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .legal-body li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    color: var(--color-gray);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .legal-body a {
    color: var(--color-black);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-lighter-gray);
  }

  .legal-body a:hover {
    border-bottom-color: var(--color-black);
  }

  .obf {
    font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Consolas, monospace;
    font-size: 0.95em;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  .sr-only {
    position: absolute;
    width: 1px;
    height: 1px;
    padding: 0;
    margin: -1px;
    overflow: hidden;
    clip: rect(0, 0, 0, 0);
    white-space: nowrap;
    border: 0;
  }
</style>
